1
00:00:00,041 --> 00:00:03,666
In the final period,
when they transferred me to the Islamic Police

2
00:00:04,625 --> 00:00:07,708
I left the prison,
then they placed me in a solitary cell

3
00:00:08,791 --> 00:00:13,000
That same day, after two or three hours,
a guard came and took me to a group cell

4
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:18,958
I saw people for the first time,
other than the dead, I saw people who were alive

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:24,125
Of course I had seen all the prisoners
who were dead, I saw them dead

6
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:30,583
When I came out, I felt like I was the only survivor
among them, me and the two people who were taken with me

7
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:37,791
We stayed in this group cell for three days
at a base in Tabqa, it was a basement

8
00:00:38,291 --> 00:00:45,791
After three days, at night there was a huge commotion
and unimaginable shelling

9
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:52,041
There was a young man, not very old,
who told me this shelling is from our area, we are the ones being shelled

10
00:00:52,541 --> 00:00:55,125
As if he was joking,
just to lighten the mood

11
00:00:56,166 --> 00:01:01,791
An official came in that I did not recognize,
his face was uncovered, he pardoned all the prisoners

12
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:07,750
Except two, a Yezidi boy
I remember from Iraq

13
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:15,500
They took him with them to Raqqa, and another person
they also took to Raqqa, what he did and what his charge was, I do not know

14
00:01:16,208 --> 00:01:20,208
Some people owed ten million lira,
or had to pay gold dinars, those were their sentences

15
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:24,708
People were waiting for their families to pay for them,
some had not paid but were pardoned anyway

16
00:01:25,291 --> 00:01:33,125
When my turn came, I went in to this person,
he was Iraqi by nationality and accent, that is all I know about him

17
00:01:33,708 --> 00:01:35,416
Interviewer: Do you remember
what this person looked like?

18
00:01:35,458 --> 00:01:40,791
He was between 45 and 50 years old,
he had a calm face

19
00:01:41,291 --> 00:01:47,375
He seemed like a very gentle person
and he gave us a sense of security

20
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:52,041
When they took me to him, there were two standing
behind me and two standing behind him

21
00:01:53,166 --> 00:02:00,208
They warned me not to get too close,
stand where we tell you, and I knew the ones behind him carried rifles

22
00:02:00,958 --> 00:02:05,833
I expected that any wrong move from me
and they would shoot me

23
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,833
He asked me, what is your name?
What do you do? Why were you brought here?

24
00:02:10,208 --> 00:02:17,250
I told him, I was accused of speaking
about the brothers in the Islamic State

25
00:02:17,291 --> 00:02:25,291
And about a certain figure in the Islamic State,
he said, I give you my word of safety, did you speak or not, my son?

26
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:29,958
I said no, I did not speak, he said, be honest with me,
I have given you my word of safety, nobody can touch you

27
00:02:30,625 --> 00:02:35,375
I said yes, I spoke, and after all that torture
I confessed to him

28
00:02:35,916 --> 00:02:39,833
He said, you are sentenced,
we will whip you 100 lashes, and then you are free

29
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:44,791
The person I spoke about,
he told me, you do not know this person the way I do

30
00:02:44,916 --> 00:02:48,125
He was a very high-ranking figure,
I cannot mention his name

31
00:02:49,208 --> 00:02:53,666
Because to this day
I live in fear of them, to this very moment

32
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:59,833
He told me that this person is a good and simple man
and that he personally sits with him and knows him

33
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:06,000
At that point I realized this person
was a senior figure in ISIS with wide influence

34
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:10,166
He told me, we will whip you 100 lashes
and then you go free

35
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:14,791
When I got out, I was hoping the guard
at the other base would be the one to whip me

36
00:03:15,875 --> 00:03:20,625
But it happened that Abu Abdullah the interrogator
was there, he is the one who whipped me 100 lashes

37
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:25,416
Of course he whipped me with vicious cruelty,
I even left barefoot

38
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:31,541
When we left for home,
we all left barefoot, without shoes

39
00:03:32,208 --> 00:03:37,333
I left and went home
and sat there and did not go out again

40
00:03:38,083 --> 00:03:44,083
I spent two days treating my injuries
and wounds from the whipping, the pain was unbearable

41
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:50,375
Of course the psychological damage was greater
than the physical pain, it still affects me a little to this day
